[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Nuffield Health Bond, launched May 2013, is a five-year fixed-term product, offering a fixed annual return of 6% (gross) in cash, for investments of £1,000 - £250,000. Our initial aim, to raise £15m, was reached early due to a phenomenal response that 
[normal]resulted in the Bond being over-subscribed - a gratifying endorsement of the Nuffield Health proposition in a depressed bond market. Ultimately the Bond raised £18m to help us make a real difference to the future of healthcare. 
[normal]19.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Nuffield Health has the bes
[normal]t balance sheet in the private health sector (compared to gym or private hospital operators). We are the least leveraged businesses in the industry and our debt represents less than 25% of our overall value. Alexander Harrison, Director Strategic Debt Fina
[normal]nce, Barclays Commercial Bank, 2008: “Nuffield Health has a very strong balance sheet with a low ratio of debt relative to the sector, further reinforcing their market position.”
