[normal]Personal fitness and wellbeing[bold]57.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Our proposition is unique. Everyone who joins our fitness and well
[normal]being 
[normal]centres
[normal] receives a clinically-governed Health MOT covering 12 risk areas. This translates into an easily understandable health score, indicating personal levels of health, enabling beneficiaries to address any issues thus taking control of their heal
[normal]th future: the essence of preventative healthcare. Helping people to help themselves is central to meeting the myriad challenges, such as the obesity epidemic, that the UK’s healthcare sector currently faces. We strive to lead that agenda.
[normal]58.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The only consume
[normal]r fitness and wellbeing service in the UK: 65 sites.
[normal]59.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The only national chain of independent physiotherapists in the UK: 130 
[normal]centres
[normal] and 2,000 physiotherapists.
[normal]60.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We invented the Health MOT as an integrated aspect of fitness and wellbeing 
[normal]programmes
[normal].
[normal]61.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]100,000+
[normal] Health MOTs, delivered 2012. 
[normal]62.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Our research reveals that more than 75% of our members, who have a Health MOT, achieve a measurable improvement in their health. 54% reduced their cholesterol; 57% improved their blood pressure; 35% lost more than 3% of their
[normal] body weight.
[normal]63.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Vi4 health assessments recorded a 17% decrease in obesity, blood pressure and cholesterol. 
[normal]64.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Research from our assessments revealed:
[normal]9%+ of clients had recorded abnormal cardiovascular investigations, including significantly narrowed arteries,
[normal] irregular heart patterns or other abnormalities.
[normal]6%+ of female clients had abnormal mammograms requiring further investigation (10% of these cases were classified as urgent).
[normal]3%+ had abnormal prostate-specific antigen tests and over 5% had abnormal cervic
[normal]al smears.
[normal]65.
