[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Remuneration[bold]68.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Nuffield Health has a Remuneration Committee, comprising trustees of the cha
[normal]rity, which takes independent advice from external advisors. It ensures that senior executives and other employees receive the necessary development and leadership opportunities, and are appropriately motivated and rewarded for their individual and collect
[normal]ive contributions to the 
[normal]organisation’s
[normal] overall performance. 
[normal]69.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]With respect to executive remuneration, the Committee has delegated authority from Nuffield Health’s Board of Governors to determine the remuneration package for all senior executives including 
[normal]the Chief Executive.
[normal]70.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Nuffield Health remuneration package: total compensation, including pension contributions, bonuses and other benefits, is positioned at 75% of the market median (median rate, discounted by 25%) for the reference market. [E.G. if there
[normal] are 11 companies in the comparative market group for a role, and the total compensation level for each company is ranked from lowest to highest, the median level is that of the company positioned in the middle at 6th place. We benchmark at this point and 
[normal]then apply a further 25% discount to determine the level of remuneration].
[normal]71.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Current reference market is a selection of companies based on comparable 
[normal]organisational
[normal] size and complexity. 
[normal]72.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Committee informed of total compensation levels in private and public h
[normal]ealthcare 
[normal]organisations
[normal], and leading charities of a comparable size, to gauge relative positioning of executive packages. 
[normal]73.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Our trustees conduct an independent annual review of executive remuneration and view the salaries of our executives as being at the a
[normal]ppropriate level to attract and retain the talent required to sustain the success of the charity. 
[normal]74.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We believe that a charity should be transparent so all of our pay levels are published in our Annual Report and Accounts.
